
[1]suppliant

   SUP'PLIANT, a. [L. supplico, to supplicate; sub and plico, to fold. See
   Comply and Apply.]

   1. Entreating; beseeching; supplicating; asking earnestly and
   submissively.

   The rich grow suppliant, and the poor grow proud.

   2. Manifesting entreaty; expressive of humble supplication.

   To bow and sue for grace with suppliant knee.

     SUP'PLIANT, n. A humble petitioner; one who entreats submissively.

   Spare this life, and hear thy suppliant's pray'r.
     __________________________________________________________________

